e economy, the American Solidarity Party might fit. |archive-date=2018-11-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181116210537/https://home.isi.org/why-you-should-vote-third-party |dead-url=no }}</ref><ref name=CDMagazine2012>{{cite web|url=http://www.christiandemocracymagazine.com/2012/12/an-interview-with-david-frost-and-kirk.html|title=An Interview with David Frost and Kirk Morrison|publisher=Christian Democracy Magazine|language=en|accessdate=23 June 2016|quote=There is a growing movement of people who adhere to Catholic Social Teaching and, because of that, find that they cannot find a home with either of the two major political parties in the United States. Their answer has been to form a political party based on Christian democratic principles. The name they have chosen is American Solidarity Party. ... Kirk, you have an article that will go into the first issue of Christian Democracy along with this interview. Christian democracy has been described as conservative on social issues and liberal on economic issues.|archive-date=2021-03-07|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210307065531/https://www.christiandemocracymagazine.com/2012/12/an-interview-with-david-frost-and-kirk.html/|dead-url=no}}</ref>及{{le|分產主義|Distributism|經濟分配主義}}<ref name="McPherson">{{citation |title=The Politics of Solidarity: The Case for the American Solidarity Party |last=McPherson |first=David |date=29 July 2016 |journal=[[First_Things|First Things]] |url=http://www.firstthings.com/blogs/firstthoughts/2016/07/the-politics-of-solidarity-a-case-for-the-american-solidarity-party |language=en |accessdate=29 July 2016 |archive-date=2021-01-16 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20210116094235/https://www.firstthings.com/blogs/firstthoughts/2016/07/the-politics-of-solidarity-a-case-for-the-american-solidarity-party |dead-url=no }}</ref>，於墮胎、死刑和安樂死堅持{{le|美國生命自主運動|United States pro-life movement|生命自主}}的社會保守立場<ref name="CruxFerry">{{citation |title=The American Solidarity Party 